Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.33,0:00:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Vershen, I'm am AVFoundation
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.24,0:00:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,engineer at Apple.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.94,0:00:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is session 515 which is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.01,0:00:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,about HLS authoring and the HLS
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.29,0:00:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.97,0:00:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,HLS is an abbreviation for HTTP
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.69,0:00:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Live Streaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.90,0:00:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,HLS is the way you stream
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.70,0:00:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,content to all Apple devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.82,0:00:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to be talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.94,0:00:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the document HLS Authoring
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.46,0:00:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Specification for Apple Devices
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.00,0:00:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and the tools we distribute for
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.37,0:00:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,creating and validating HLS
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.00,0:00:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,content.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.64,0:00:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The Authoring Specification and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.41,0:00:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,other important documents about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.32,0:00:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,HLS can be found at this URL
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.35,0:00:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,developer.apple.com/streaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.49,0:00:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The Authoring Specification is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.33,0:01:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple's advice for authoring HLS
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.34,0:01:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,content.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.03,0:01:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted the HLS specification,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.88,0:01:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the Internet draft, to include
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.13,0:01:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,only absolutely necessary
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.68,0:01:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,requirements.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.25,0:01:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The Authoring Specification, on
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.63,0:01:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the other hand, includes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.76,0:01:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,requirements that are specific
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.00,0:01:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to Apple's players, as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.02,0:01:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,things that, while not
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.07,0:01:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,absolutely required, are part of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.91,0:01:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,best practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.32,0:01:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The big news this year is we've
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.02,0:01:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,added support for HEVC.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.14,0:01:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are the limits on what is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.41,0:01:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,playable.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.31,0:01:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Main 10 Profile, Level 5.0, High
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.78,0:01:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Tier.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.73,0:01:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that we support HEVC content
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.36,0:01:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,we've added bit rate guidelines
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.75,0:01:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,for that as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.53,0:01:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You should treat those
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.14,0:01:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,recommendations as very
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.33,0:01:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,preliminary.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.56,0:01:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,HEVC encoders are still
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.34,0:01:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,evolving, we expect to see
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.20,0:01:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,improvements over time so we may
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.86,0:01:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,revise our guidelines in the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.12,0:01:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,future.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.00,0:01:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You should also remember that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.08,0:01:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the bit rate recommendations in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.45,0:01:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the Authoring Specification are
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.53,0:01:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,guidelines, they are not cast in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.23,0:01:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.51,0:01:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We are aware that all content is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.11,0:02:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,different, a bit rate that works
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.82,0:02:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,for a video of two people
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.81,0:02:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,talking is not likely to work
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.73,0:02:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,for a sporting event.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.27,0:02:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And you may have different
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.37,0:02:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints on the number of bit
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.45,0:02:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,rate variants that you can
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.35,0:02:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,provide.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.25,0:02:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, use the bit rate guidelines
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.69,0:02:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,as a starting point.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.68,0:02:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Having HEVC means that you can
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.49,0:02:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,have both H.264 and HEVC content
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.36,0:02:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in the same master playlist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.17,0:02:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we've come up with some best
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.52,0:02:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,practices.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.51,0:02:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,First and most important, always
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.70,0:02:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,use the CODECS attribute.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.63,0:02:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You need this so that older
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.01,0:02:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,players don't try to play the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.36,0:02:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,HEVC content.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.16,0:02:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Second and almost as important,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.23,0:02:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,always include some H.264
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.10,0:02:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,content.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.16,0:02:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You need this so older players
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.52,0:02:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,will have something that they
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.38,0:02:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,can play.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.72,0:02:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the player will switch
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.61,0:02:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,between H.264 and HEVC.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.50,0:02:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,However, for two variants with
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.14,0:02:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,similar bit rates the player
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.49,0:02:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,will typically favor the HEVC
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.93,0:02:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,content.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.45,0:02:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,While H.264 content could be in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.53,0:02:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,FMP4 files for maximum
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.66,0:02:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,compatibility keep your H.264 in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.91,0:03:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,transport streams.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.14,0:03:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The last point I want to make is
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.82,0:03:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that these same rules apply to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.61,0:03:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,so-called trick play content,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.02,0:03:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that is I-frame-only content.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.73,0:03:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Along with adding HEVC support
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.83,0:03:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,we also added support for a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.43,0:03:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,second subtitle format, IMSC.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.77,0:03:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want more detail on our
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.33,0:03:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,support for IMSC1 you should
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.07,0:03:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,look at this year's Advances in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.77,0:03:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,HTTP Live Streaming talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.41,0:03:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,IMSC1 is based on TTML, the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.59,0:03:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,timed text markup language and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.62,0:03:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it's compatible with standards
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.10,0:03:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,from the EBU and SMPTE.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.61,0:03:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about best practices
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.60,0:03:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,for subtitle content.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.98,0:03:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We support the text profile of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.67,0:03:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,IMSC and note that IMSC content
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.19,0:03:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,must be in fragmented MP4 files,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.43,0:03:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't use plaintext files.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.35,0:03:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,WebVTT is the same as it has
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.21,0:03:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,been, text files typically
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.00,0:03:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,having an extension of .VTT or
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.46,0:03:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,.webVTT.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.13,0:03:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that you can mix up
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.52,0:04:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,IMSC and webVTT with H.264 HEVC
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.56,0:04:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,content however you want,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.21,0:04:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,they're completely independent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.02,0:04:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You should always use the IMSC1
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.47,0:04:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,CODECS value.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.02,0:04:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Including that value ensures
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.58,0:04:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that older clients will ignore
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.04,0:04:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the variant.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.90,0:04:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,However, for maximum backward
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.25,0:04:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,compatibilities don't put in the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.05,0:04:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,value for the webVTT content.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.41,0:04:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to change gears and talk
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.90,0:04:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,about the HLS tools and the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.27,0:04:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,changes we've made there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.23,0:04:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The tools are available on the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.42,0:04:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,developer site and you can find
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.92,0:04:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,them through the same URL I
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.67,0:04:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,mentioned earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.73,0:04:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,developer.apple.com/streaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.25,0:04:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The tools fall into three rough
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.67,0:04:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,categories, tools for segmenting
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.73,0:04:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,video and audio, tools for
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.75,0:04:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,validating content and making
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.18,0:04:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,validation reports and finally,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.53,0:04:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,tools for creating subtitles,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.30,0:04:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,iv3 metadata and master
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.45,0:04:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,playlists.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.76,0:04:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the validator does not do
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.39,0:04:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,low-level bitstream checks, you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.07,0:04:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,should be using third-party
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.24,0:04:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,tools if you think you may have
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.54,0:04:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,issues with your encoders.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.81,0:04:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at some of the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.58,0:04:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,specific changes we made in the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.08,0:04:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.40,0:05:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well firstly, we've added the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.04,0:05:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,ability for MediaStreamValidator
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.06,0:05:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to check local files.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.77,0:05:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You no longer have to put an
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.85,0:05:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,HTTP server to validate your
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.54,0:05:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,streams.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.21,0:05:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have direct file access
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.36,0:05:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you can check them that way and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.78,0:05:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you can use relative paths,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.30,0:05:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute paths or file URLs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.05,0:05:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I should note that you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.48,0:05:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,can't mix file URLs and HTTP,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.59,0:05:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that is if the master playlist
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.90,0:05:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is a file path then the media
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.67,0:05:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,playlist it references can't be
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.02,0:05:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,HTTP URLs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.02,0:05:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we added support for
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.65,0:05:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,HEVC into the tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.30,0:05:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We've also made a lot of general
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.86,0:05:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,improvements to the tools,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.29,0:05:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,principally the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.78,0:05:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,MediaStreamValidator and HLS
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.52,0:05:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,report.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.72,0:05:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We check more things about the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.89,0:05:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.80,0:05:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There are too many to list, but
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.07,0:05:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,for example, we're now
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.99,0:05:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,validating the CODEC usage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.51,0:05:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We have better handling for
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.65,0:05:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,errors on the stream during
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.88,0:05:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,validation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.17,0:05:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And we made the ordering of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.29,0:05:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,variants renditions in the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.50,0:05:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,reports be more consistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.34,0:05:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We've added several new options,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.05,0:05:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to call out just three of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.33,0:05:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.79,0:06:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,First, the description option on
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.39,0:06:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,MediaStreamValidator.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.52,0:06:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The URLs for a stream don't
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.82,0:06:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,necessarily make clear what the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.17,0:06:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,content is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.50,0:06:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This option allows you to add
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.70,0:06:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,some text describing the stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.58,0:06:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, such and such show,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.13,0:06:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,season two, episode five.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.12,0:06:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The text will appear at the top
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.39,0:06:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of the report near the URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.20,0:06:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,For HLS report, we've added some
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.79,0:06:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,new optional columns.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.21,0:06:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than continue the way we
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.38,0:06:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,had previously with separate
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.69,0:06:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,options for each column, instead
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.72,0:06:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we've added a columns option
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.39,0:06:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that takes a list of column and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.52,0:06:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,identifiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.05,0:06:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The set of available column
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.39,0:06:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,identifiers can be found using
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.80,0:06:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the Help option or in the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.34,0:06:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] page.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.75,0:06:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The old id and pl options that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.92,0:06:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,gave you data id values and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.74,0:06:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,playlist bit rates are still
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.90,0:06:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,supported, but are deprecated in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.55,0:06:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,favor of column identifiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.73,0:06:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And the column identifiers for
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.99,0:06:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,those are just id and pl.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.38,0:06:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Last year we added hdcp-level
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.96,0:06:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,support, but we forgot to tell
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.47,0:06:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you about the hdcp-level option
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.85,0:06:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,on MediaFileSegmenter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.82,0:07:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This allows you to set the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.54,0:07:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,hdcp-level.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.14,0:07:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The hdcp-level is included in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.07,0:07:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the Plist that gets generated by
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.66,0:07:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,MediaFileSegmenter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.49,0:07:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can pass that Plist to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.01,0:07:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the variant playlist creator to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.55,0:07:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,get the hdcp-level attribute in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.85,0:07:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the generated master playlist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.88,0:07:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a quick look of a sample
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.36,0:07:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,report.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.63,0:07:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice the second line, that's
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.56,0:07:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,from the description option that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.70,0:07:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,we passed in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.23,0:07:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,MediaStreamValidator.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.76,0:07:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And notice that we've now added
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.96,0:07:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,a CODECS column so you can see
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.21,0:07:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,which variants are H.264 and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.58,0:07:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,HEVC.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.22,0:07:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we use the AVC, the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.23,0:07:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,alternate name of H.264 so that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.43,0:07:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll have more visible
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.40,0:07:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,separation between the two CODEC
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.89,0:07:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,types.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.52,0:07:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,As part of the changes in the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.10,0:07:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,ordering of variants and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.01,0:07:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,renditions, we now keep audio,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.92,0:07:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,closed caption and subtitle
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.13,0:07:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,renditions separate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.37,0:07:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,To summarize, remember that URL,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.04,0:08:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,developer.apple.com/streaming,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.01,0:08:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,everything you need to know is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.25,0:08:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,pointed to from that page.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.11,0:08:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides the various documents it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.46,0:08:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,also has links to sample
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.67,0:08:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,streams, to the tools download,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.14,0:08:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to past videos about HLS, the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.25,0:08:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,information about FairPlay
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.31,0:08:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Streaming and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.43,0:08:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I encourage you all to read the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.56,0:08:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,HLS Authoring Specification for
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.95,0:08:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Devices and the HLS spec.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.73,0:08:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,For more information go to the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.50,0:08:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,webpage for this talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.09,0:08:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,developer.apple.com/WWDC17/515.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.23,0:08:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We have some related video
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.60,0:08:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,sessions, Advances in HTTP Live
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.42,0:08:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Streaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.78,0:08:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This has more discussion of HEVC
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.19,0:08:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and IMSC1, as well as some other
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.65,0:08:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting topics.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.21,0:08:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And Error Handling Best
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.71,0:08:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Practices for HTTP Live
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.36,0:08:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Streaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.81,0:08:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That will help you understand
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.47,0:08:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,what your server needs to do to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.31,0:08:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,be a good HLS server.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.59,0:08:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You can watch either of these
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.98,0:08:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,videos via the web or in the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.84,0:08:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,WWDC app.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.79,0:09:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you found the talk
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.14,0:09:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,useful, thanks for watching.
